This paper deals with deep learning and image classification, which are topics commonly found in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of neural networks and optimization techniques also suggests the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on synthetic aperture radar (SAR) images, which are a type of remote sensing data, making the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category a possibility. Finally, the paper's emphasis on optimizing the network's performance suggests the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category as a potential fit.
